    "The authors demonstrated different approaches for this model to generate structures.",
    "For example, in the first task, the model was trained to generate molecules with specific structural constraints, e.g., structures devoid of sulfur atoms.",
    "This shows the adaptability of the model to such structural constraints in the prediction.",
    "In a second task, the model was trained to generate molecules similar to a query structure, e.g., the Celecoxib drug.",
    "This showcases the capacity of the model for scaffold hopping and library expansion, demonstrating its utility in diversifying chemical space starting from a single reference molecule."
